author: Jon Stone
description: The Information Commissioner has launched a formal inquiry into political parties’ use of data analytics to target voters amid concerns that Britons’ privacy could be put at risk by new campaign tactics. Elizabeth Denham, the Information Commissioner, warned there were “data protection risks” from politicians increasingly using voters’ personal data and that campaigning tools were having “a significant potential impact on individuals’ privacy”.
title: Information Commissioner launches inquiry into misuse of personal data by political parties
